##################################################
To import the project into eclipse
##################################################
- open a new shell
- cd mp4
- mvn eclipse:eclipse
- open eclipse
- import existing project navigate to mp4
- import 'docs/codestyle.xml' as eclipse Java code style

##################################################
To Run the sample from eclipse
##################################################

- open eclipse
- import launch configurations: File > Import... > Run/Debug > Launch Configurations
- browse to src/test/resources/sample
- select all three (Node1.launch, Node2.launch, NodeConsole.launch)
- launch the two Node launch configs
- run NodeConsole launch config
- verify output under /tmp/node1 and /tmp/node2

##################################################
Extensions implemented
##################################################

1. support for user-defined map reduce functions
2. support custom input format for splitting input files and reading split records
3. support for more than 2 nodes
4. ability to execute arbitrary number of jobs concurrently on different nodes
5. runtime properties configurable, e.g. number of threads, heartbeat interval etc.
6. jobs configurable, e.g. input split size, output key/value separator
7. console that can connect to to any node and execute commands
8. display total time, wait time, running time for each job, task, and attempt
9. bootstrap policy for initial task distribution
10. pluggable policy framework